  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He complained I'm sitting too straight, then it's almost [NON-ENGLISH] So this-- this went together with a-- with a good feeling of Shabbos too, a Shabbos meal, as well always.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Shabbos meal, there was always very, very happy occasions and feelings.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was spiritually, that we didn't realize even then that it was spiritually.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was spiritual.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But there was always plenty good food, Shabbos food and [NON-ENGLISH] in our house.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Other people, we, we-- my mother used to send me or my sister to about six to 10 people with a half a chicken, or with a challah, or two challahs, that really didn't have Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Didn't have-- and other people did that too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I, I go from our house.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Half a chicken, in some case [INAUDIBLE] because a single fellow, was a quarter of a chicken, a half a chicken and-- and some challahs.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pesach was, everybody was in such a spirit that it's hard to explain spiritual things, you know, the spiritual feeling because first of all, the weeks before, everybody was busy.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All this food were out on tables to get some air.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In case of chametz, you should throw away, the wind should blow it away.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Almost everybody was painting.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And everybody was busy before Pesach.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then a few days before Pesach, first of all, the matzahs baker-- there was only one bakery.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And most of the poor people were working there, especially the women and the elder girls made a few dollars then.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was for them, the-- once a year, the-- the-- the so called earning time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there was-- the-- the whole spirit was there with them packing the matzahs, taking home the matzahs was-- This was the thing of the-- of the town.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
